Description. Male (
IBSP
166778).

Carapace and chelicerae reddish brown (
Fig. 22A
). Endites brownish yellow; labium dark brownish yellow. Sternum brownish yellow, with darker margins, marbled with dark pigment, and three pairs of dark marginal areas, the hind one fainted (
Fig. 22B
). Palps brownish orange (
Fig. 23A‒B
). Legs brownish yellow, pairs I‒II darker with dark pigment forming diffuse rings in the distal region of metatarsus and tarsus (
Fig. 22C‒E
). Abdomen withish grey, with a conspicuous dark dorsal pattern comprising arrow-shaped marks (
Fig. 22A‒B
). Total length 6.64; carapace 3.4 long, 2.16 wide. Chelicerae not projected (
Fig. 22A
). Palps: bulb elliptical, mid-portion slightly shorter than the embolus; embolus tubular, tapered, and abruptly curved; tibia short and slightly incrassated, almost cylindrical, with the dorso-ventral diameter almost equal to the bulb (
Fig. 23A‒B
). Legs: robust and coated with setae (
Fig. 22C‒E
); tarsal brush of putative chemosensory setae present in legs I‒IV, but reduced in legs I, III and IV. Leg formula: I-II-IV-III. Leg measurements: I, femur 3.16, patella 1,.2, tibia 2.6, metatarsus 3.04, tarsus 0.8, total 10.8; II, 2.88, 1.16, 2.6, 2.8, 0.76, 10.2; III, 2.0, 0.96, 1.56, 1.84, 0.64, 7.0; IV, 2.56, 1.24, 2.04, 2.0, 0.6, 8.44. Macrosetae: I, femur D0-0-0-1-1-1/0-2-0, P0-0-0-0-0-2-1-0; tibia P0-1-0-1- 0-1-0, vp1-0-1-0-1-0-1, vr2-0-1-0-1-0-1, R1-1-1-1-1-1-0; metatarsus p0-1-0-0-0-0-0-0, vp0-1-0-0-1-0-0-1, vr0-1- 0-0-1-0-0-1, r0-1-0-0-0-0-0-0 (
Fig. 22C‒E
); II, femur D0-0-1-1-1-0-2-0, P0-0-0-0-0-1-1-0; tibia P0-1-0-1-0-1-0, vp1-0-1-0-1-0-1, vr2-0-1-0-1-0-1, R1-1-0/1-1-0/1-1-0; metatarsus p0-1-0-0-0-0-0-0, vp0-1-0-0-1-0-0-1, vr0-1-0-0- 1-0-0-1, r0-1-0-1-0-1-0-0; IV, femur D0/1-1-1-0-1-1-0-1-0-0-0; tibia vp0-0/1-0-0-0-0-0, vr0-0-0-0-0-0-0/1; metatarsus vp0-0-0/1-0-0-0-2, vr metatarsal comb with 4 macrosetae.

Female (
IBSP
166779).

